-- Russian Stocks Pare Weekly Drop as Germany Data Lifts Crude Oil
-- B y   D e n i s   M a t e r n o v s k y
-- 2012-04-20T15:26:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/russian-stocks-head-for-weekly-drop-on-europe-economy-concern.html
Russian stocks rose, erasing their
weekly drop, as an unexpected increase in German business
confidence pushed oil to its first gain in three days.  The  Micex Index (VTBMICX)  of 30 shares added 0.6 percent to 1,505.10
as of 6:45 p.m. in Moscow, bringing this week’s gain to 0.2
percent. The gauge fell as much as 0.8 percent earlier today.
Oil producer OAO Surgutneftegas added 3.6 percent, the strongest
advance on the index today, while OAO RusHydro,  Russia ’s biggest
hydropower generator, gained 2.9 percent.  The Russian Depositary
Index (RDXUSD)  of London-traded shares of Russian companies added 0.9
percent to 1,778.11.  Oil futures surged as much as 2 percent to $104.27 a
barrel, rising for the first time in three days in New York. The
Munich-based Ifo institute said today its business climate index
rose to 109.9 from 109.8, while economists forecast a drop to
109.5. Oil and gas account for about 50 percent of Russian
government revenue.  “ Germany ’s not only Europe’s largest economy, it’s also
Russia’s second most important trading partner after  China ,”
Peter Westin, chief strategist at Aton LLC in Moscow, said by e-
mail. “Good data in Germany does affect Russia.”  OAO Rosneft, Russia’s biggest oil company, rose 0.6 percent
to 216.54 rubles, its highest level since March 16. Preferred
shares of Surgutneftegas rose to 20.125 rubles, its highest
closing level since April 4. Russia’s fourth-biggest oil
producer will publish this year’s results to international
standards and dividends will grow, Deputy General Director
Vyacheslav Nikiforov told journalists in Moscow today.  The  Market Vectors Russia ETF (RSX) , a U.S.-traded fund that
holds Russian shares, rose 1.7 percent to $30.49 in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denis Maternovsky in Moscow at 
